HEADWORD: kephalin
<hw>keph"a*lin</hw> <pr>(k⟦ecr⟧f"⟦adot⟧*l⟦icr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>kefalh`</grk> the head; it was supposed by
<person>Thudichum</person> to exist in brain tissue.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>One of a group of phospholipids
(nitrogenous phosphorized fatty substances), present in all living cells
and particularly noticeable in nervous tissue. Same as
<er>cephalin</er>, which see.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

